# Frontend Architecture

- Treat `localpaas-dashboard/` as the frontend project root.
- Keep feature code inside the owning module under `src/application/modules/<module>`.
- Use `src/application/shared` only for cross-module UI, hooks, pages, layouts, dialogs, constants, and data utilities.
- Use `src/infrastructure` for framework/client primitives, API plumbing, exceptions, device services, and generic data types.
- Avoid editing `src/components/ui` for one-off screen needs; wrap or compose primitives nearby instead.
- Keep module-owned constants, schemas, entities, and components in the module until at least two modules need the same abstraction.

# File And Folder Shape

- Components use `*.com.tsx`; colocate complex scoped styles as `*.module.scss`.
- Table columns and static table helpers belong in `*.defs.tsx`.
- Shared or exported props/types belong in `*.types.ts`.
- Routes usually have `route/`, optional `form/`, `schemas/`, `types/`, and `building-blocks/` folders.
- Modules expose public surfaces through `index.ts` barrels and module aggregators such as `<module>.module.ts`.
- New public module files must be exported through the nearest `index.ts`; routes and layouts must also be exported by the module aggregator used for lazy loading.

# Imports

- Use aliases from `tsconfig.app.json`: `@application/*`, `~/*` for `src/application/modules/*`, `@assets/*`, and `@/*`.
- Prefer module-local imports through `~/<module>/...` for module-owned code.
- Prefer `@application/shared/...` for shared application code and `@infrastructure/...` for infrastructure code.
- Let Prettier sort imports; do not hand-fight import grouping.
- Use type-only imports for types.
- Do not import across sibling modules unless using a deliberate shared/public surface.

# TypeScript And React

- Do not declare new TypeScript enums; prefer existing enums or `as const` objects/unions.
- Keep explicit module boundary types where lint requires them.
- Use function declarations for named React components.
- Keep hooks dependency arrays correct; do not silence `react-hooks/exhaustive-deps`.
- Keep server-state in TanStack Query and local dialog/UI state in existing local state patterns.
- Keep component props narrow and domain-named; avoid leaking API request/response types into UI props.

# Styling

- Prefer Tailwind utilities for normal layout and component composition.
- Use SCSS modules for complex scoped styling only.
- Keep global CSS changes limited to app-wide tokens/resets.
- Use `lucide-react` icons when an icon button or action needs a standard icon.
